# NES.css Styling

## NesCss Object
Central class-name strings in `common/nescss/NesCss.scala`: `container`, `containerRounded`, `btn`, `btnPrimary`, `btnError`, `text`, `input`, `radio`. Always use these constants, not raw strings.

## Custom Cursor
NES.css uses a pixel-art hand cursor for `a` and `button`. For any custom clickable element, use `cursor: var(--nes-pointer)` (defined in `:root` in `css/style.css`) -- **not** `cursor: pointer`.

## Press Start 2P Font
- **Page:** Loaded via `@font-face` in `css/style.css` from `assets/PressStart2P-Regular.ttf` with `font-display: swap`.
- **PDF:** Uses `assets/fontData.js` which sets `window.pressStartBase64`. Loaded in `index.html` before app.
- **Caveat:** Font lacks checkmark glyph; native checkboxes render blank ticks. Use NES.css radio buttons (Off/On) instead of checkboxes.

## NES.css Radio Buttons
`input.nes-radio` + **immediate sibling `span`** with label text (NES.css draws dot via `input:checked + span::before`). Use `onClick` (not `onInput`) to update model. Wrap group in `div.stacked-radios`; each `label.stacked-radio-option` gets `cursor: var(--nes-pointer)`.

## Layout Stability
- `#myapp` and `.screen-container` use `width: 42rem; max-width: 100%` to prevent layout jumps between screens.
- `html { scrollbar-gutter: stable }` prevents scrollbar-induced layout shift.

## Theming
CSS variables in `css/style.css` control theming (e.g. `--palette-element-bg`, `--palette-frame`, `--screen-container-bg`). Theme variants (e.g. `body.theme-gameboy`) override these variables.
